reducing rear visibility.

the vehicle experiences difficulty shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal Hardness and Anti-Lock Braking System (ABS) Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal to function properly and the ABS system to engage can lead to increased stopping distances, loss of control, and accidents, potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels hard to press
the brake pedal does not respond as expected
the ABS system does not engage
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration while using cruise control can lead to a loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly while cruise control is activated

the vehicle speed increases without driver input.
